name: The Climbing Hangar Matchworks
directions: go in past the tills, and on the far right of the building there are 2 gender neutral stalls next to the womens bathroom
comment: probably have to be a customer, but if you are nice and ask im sure theyll let you in. Ive been going to The Hangar for years and they are a really nice centre and very lgbt posotive; FYI there is an lgbt meetup here every other friday, so check that out!

name: SuperValu Finglas
directions:
Go in the main door and through the exit on the right. There's a small newsagents type layout. Walk past that and there's a single unisex toilet on the right. 
If you go in the doors on the left, walk through the supermarket and out past the tills.
comment: It doesn't always have toilet paper. Bring your own tissues. It's not a very nice toilet but it's unisex and free so it'll do.

name: Costa Coffee, Finglas
directions: Down the back, through the door, on the left. There are at least two decently sized individual unisex bathrooms with a toilet and sink in each.
comment: You need a code to get through the door. It's been 1234 the couple of times I've been there. The door is sometimes open as it leads to the staff area.

name: McClelland Hall
directions: Second floor, east side. If you're entering from Helen street, go up the stairs or ramp to the atrium, go left down the hallway, you'll come to an open area with chairs and tables and there should be a set of double doors with a sign for restrooms (they are to the right of a different set of double doors), the restrooms are past the vending machines, the gender neutral bathroom is single stall and between the women's and men's bathrooms.
comment: McClelland hall is open Monday - Friday 7 AM to 6 PM | Saturday Closed. | Sunday Closed, and closed during University holidays

name: Subway
directions: directly at the back of the Subway. one single stall, not gendered, no changing table.
comment: If you are desperate, you can go in and use the restroom and just walk right out. They do not require any purchase for restroom usage. I would be careful, as the owner is transphobic and homophobic, but if you're just in and out, there should be no issues.

name: Petco
directions: all the way in the back, far left corner, small hallway, wheelchair accessible, gendered single stall bathrooms, both with a changing table
comment: I am a Petco employee and am trans. Also work with another trans man. The company is very accepting and loving towards our community. If you ever feel threatened by any customers or generally unsafe, please find a Petco employee. We will be more than happy to make sure you are in no danger, even if that requires removing a threat (customer) from our store. Stay safe!
